description: Lists your target groups. You can narrow your search by using the filters below in your request.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the target group.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that the target group was created, in ISO-8601 format.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the target group.

nested_items.name: ipAddressType
nested_items.description: The type of IP address used for the target group. The possible values are IPV4 and IPV6. This is an optional parameter. If not specified, the default is IPV4.

nested_items.name: lambdaEventStructureVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the event structure that your Lambda function receives. Supported only if the target group type is LAMBDA.

nested_items.name: lastUpdatedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that the target group was last updated, in ISO-8601 format.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the target group.

nested_items.name: port
nested_items.description: The port of the target group.

nested_items.name: protocol
nested_items.description: The protocol of the target group.

nested_items.name: serviceArns
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) of the service.

nested_items.name: vpcIdentifier
nested_items.description: The ID of the VPC of the target group.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If there are additional results, a pagination token for the next page of results.
